=Support for editing Lua Code=

lua-mode.el with syntax highlighting, auto-indent, interactive Lua shell, paren and brace matching, auto-move to function or block begin/end can be found at [http://lua-users.org/files/wiki_insecure/editors/lua-mode.el]. More recent version is available at [http://lua-mode.luaforge.net/]

Note the current lua-mode.el is a bit screwed up with regard to usual emacs conventions -- in particular, it gives underscore ("_") word syntax, which can be very disconcerting to an experienced Emacs user...

=See also=
FlymakeLua -- syntax checking for Lua.

LuaBlockMode -- highlight matching block
